Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #medium saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting lid) on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the @korma curry paste{50%grams} and half the garlic, then cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @basmati rice{150%grams}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and @water for the rice{300%milliliters} into the onion pan and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, trim the @green beans{80%grams} and cut into thirds.

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved).

== Garlicky Green Beans ==

When the rice has 10 mins left, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir-fry until starting to char, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @king prawns{300%grams}. > IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

== Assembly ==

Once the beans are charred, add the prawns to the pan and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the remaining @garlic clove{1}(grated) and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then remove from the heat. > IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir through the @mango chutney{40%grams}.

Add the mango rice, lime zest and a good squeeze of lime juice to your pan of prawns and beans. Stir together until combined.

Taste and add salt, pepper and more lime juice if needed.

Spoon the prawn pilaf into #bowls{}, then top with a dollop of @low fat natural yoghurt{75%grams}.

Cut the remaining @lime{} into wedges and serve alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!